  "text": "In addition, as temporary fault always occurs on overhead HVDC line, once the fault has been cleared, the converter is required to rebuild the dc line voltage and recover the power transmission. The recovery control of HBSM based MMC with dc CB was developed in [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] , the automatic recovery control of MMC employing the HBSM with double thyristor switches was discussed in [CITATION_3] , and the fast recovery control of hybrid MMC was proposed in [CITATION_4] and [CITATION_5] . However, no discussion of the recovery control of the MDCC has been reported in the published papers.",
